#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:3
msgid "CPU build options"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:6
msgid "Description"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:8
msgid ""
"The following options are mainly used to change the default behavior of "
"optimizations that target certain CPU features:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:18
msgid "``--cpu-baseline``: minimal set of required CPU features."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:12
msgid ""
"Default value is ``min`` which provides the minimum CPU features that can "
"safely run on a wide range of platforms within the processor family."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:17
msgid ""
"During the runtime, NumPy modules will fail to load if any of specified "
"features are not supported by the target CPU (raises Python runtime error)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:27
msgid "``--cpu-dispatch``: dispatched set of additional CPU features."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:21
msgid ""
"Default value is ``max -xop -fma4`` which enables all CPU features, except "
"for AMD legacy features (in case of X86)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:26
msgid ""
"During the runtime, NumPy modules will skip any specified features that are "
"not available in the target CPU."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:29
msgid ""
"These options are accessible through :py:mod:`distutils` commands `distutils."
"command.build`, `distutils.command.build_clib` and `distutils.command."
"build_ext`. They accept a set of :ref:`CPU features <opt-supported-"
"features>` or groups of features that gather several features or :ref:"
"`special options <opt-special-options>` that perform a series of procedures."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:39
msgid ""
"If ``build_clib`` or ``build_ext`` are not specified by the user, the "
"arguments of ``build`` will be used instead, which also holds the default "
"values."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:42
msgid "To customize both ``build_ext`` and ``build_clib``::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:44
msgid ""
"cd /path/to/numpy\n"
"python setup.py build --cpu-baseline=\"avx2 fma3\" install --user"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:47
msgid "To customize only ``build_ext``::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:49
msgid ""
"cd /path/to/numpy\n"
"python setup.py build_ext --cpu-baseline=\"avx2 fma3\" install --user"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:52
msgid "To customize only ``build_clib``::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:54
msgid ""
"cd /path/to/numpy\n"
"python setup.py build_clib --cpu-baseline=\"avx2 fma3\" install --user"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:57
msgid "You can also customize CPU/build options through PIP command::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:59
msgid ""
"pip install --no-use-pep517 --global-option=build \\\n"
"--global-option=\"--cpu-baseline=avx2 fma3\" \\\n"
"--global-option=\"--cpu-dispatch=max\" ./"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:64
msgid "Quick Start"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:66
msgid ""
"In general, the default settings tend to not impose certain CPU features "
"that may not be available on some older processors. Raising the ceiling of "
"the baseline features will often improve performance and may also reduce "
"binary size."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:72
msgid ""
"The following are the most common scenarios that may require changing the "
"default settings:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:77
msgid "I am building NumPy for my local use"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:79
msgid ""
"And I do not intend to export the build to other users or target a different "
"CPU than what the host has."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:82
msgid ""
"Set `native` for baseline, or manually specify the CPU features in case of "
"option `native` isn't supported by your platform::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:85
msgid "python setup.py build --cpu-baseline=\"native\" bdist"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:87
msgid ""
"Building NumPy with extra CPU features isn't necessary for this case, since "
"all supported features are already defined within the baseline features::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:90
msgid "python setup.py build --cpu-baseline=native --cpu-dispatch=none bdist"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:94
msgid ""
"A fatal error will be raised if `native` isn't supported by the host "
"platform."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:97
msgid "I do not want to support the old processors of the `x86` architecture"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:99
msgid ""
"Since most of the CPUs nowadays support at least `AVX`, `F16C` features, you "
"can use::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:101
msgid "python setup.py build --cpu-baseline=\"avx f16c\" bdist"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:105
msgid ""
"``--cpu-baseline`` force combine all implied features, so there's no need to "
"add SSE features."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:110
msgid "I'm facing the same case above but with `ppc64` architecture"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:112
msgid "Then raise the ceiling of the baseline features to Power8::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:114
msgid "python setup.py build --cpu-baseline=\"vsx2\" bdist"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:117
msgid "Having issues with `AVX512` features?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:119
msgid ""
"You may have some reservations about including of `AVX512` or any other CPU "
"feature and you want to exclude from the dispatched features::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:122
msgid ""
"python setup.py build --cpu-dispatch=\"max -avx512f -avx512cd \\\n"
"-avx512_knl -avx512_knm -avx512_skx -avx512_clx -avx512_cnl -avx512_icl\" "
"\\\n"
"bdist"
msgstr ""

