#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:176
msgid "Behaviors"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:178
msgid "CPU features and other options are case-insensitive, for example::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:180
msgid "python setup.py build --cpu-dispatch=\"SSE41 avx2 FMA3\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:182
msgid "The order of the requested optimizations doesn't matter::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:184
msgid ""
"python setup.py build --cpu-dispatch=\"SSE41 AVX2 FMA3\"\n"
"# equivalent to\n"
"python setup.py build --cpu-dispatch=\"FMA3 AVX2 SSE41\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:188
msgid ""
"Either commas or spaces or '+' can be used as a separator, for example::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:191
msgid ""
"python setup.py build --cpu-dispatch=\"avx2 avx512f\"\n"
"# or\n"
"python setup.py build --cpu-dispatch=avx2,avx512f\n"
"# or\n"
"python setup.py build --cpu-dispatch=\"avx2+avx512f\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:197
msgid ""
"all works but arguments should be enclosed in quotes or escaped by backslash "
"if any spaces are used."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:200
msgid "``--cpu-baseline`` combines all implied CPU features, for example::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:202
msgid ""
"python setup.py build --cpu-baseline=sse42\n"
"# equivalent to\n"
"python setup.py build --cpu-baseline=\"sse sse2 sse3 ssse3 sse41 popcnt "
"sse42\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:206
msgid ""
"``--cpu-baseline`` will be treated as \"native\" if compiler native flag ``-"
"march=native`` or ``-xHost`` or ``/QxHost`` is enabled through environment "
"variable `CFLAGS`::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:210
msgid ""
"export CFLAGS=\"-march=native\"\n"
"python setup.py install --user\n"
"# is equivalent to\n"
"python setup.py build --cpu-baseline=native install --user"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:215
msgid ""
"``--cpu-baseline`` escapes any specified features that aren't supported by "
"the target platform or compiler rather than raising fatal errors."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:220
msgid ""
"Since ``--cpu-baseline`` combines all implied features, the maximum "
"supported of implied features will be enabled rather than escape all of "
"them. For example::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:224
msgid ""
"# Requesting `AVX2,FMA3` but the compiler only support **SSE** features\n"
"python setup.py build --cpu-baseline=\"avx2 fma3\"\n"
"# is equivalent to\n"
"python setup.py build --cpu-baseline=\"sse sse2 sse3 ssse3 sse41 popcnt "
"sse42\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:229
msgid ""
"``--cpu-dispatch`` does not combain any of implied CPU features, so you must "
"add them unless you want to disable one or all of them::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:232
msgid ""
"# Only dispatches AVX2 and FMA3\n"
"python setup.py build --cpu-dispatch=avx2,fma3\n"
"# Dispatches AVX and SSE features\n"
"python setup.py build --cpu-baseline=ssse3,sse41,sse42,avx,avx2,fma3"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:237
msgid ""
"``--cpu-dispatch`` escapes any specified baseline features and also escapes "
"any features not supported by the target platform or compiler without "
"raising fatal errors."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:241
msgid ""
"Eventually, you should always check the final report through the build log "
"to verify the enabled features. See :ref:`opt-build-report` for more details."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:247
msgid "Platform differences"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:249
msgid ""
"Some exceptional conditions force us to link some features together when it "
"come to certain compilers or architectures, resulting in the impossibility "
"of building them separately."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:252
msgid "These conditions can be divided into two parts, as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:254
msgid "**Architectural compatibility**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:256
msgid ""
"The need to align certain CPU features that are assured to be supported by "
"successive generations of the same architecture, some cases:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:259
msgid ""
"On ppc64le ``VSX(ISA 2.06)`` and ``VSX2(ISA 2.07)`` both imply one another "
"since the first generation that supports little-endian mode is Power-8`(ISA "
"2.07)`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:261
msgid ""
"On AArch64 ``NEON NEON_FP16 NEON_VFPV4 ASIMD`` implies each other since they "
"are part of the hardware baseline."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:264
#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:284
msgid "For example::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:266
msgid ""
"# On ARMv8/A64, specify NEON is going to enable Advanced SIMD\n"
"# and all predecessor extensions\n"
"python setup.py build --cpu-baseline=neon\n"
"# which equivalent to\n"
"python setup.py build --cpu-baseline=\"neon neon_fp16 neon_vfpv4 asimd\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:274
msgid ""
"Please take a deep look at :ref:`opt-supported-features`, in order to "
"determine the features that imply one another."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:277
msgid "**Compilation compatibility**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:279
msgid ""
"Some compilers don't provide independent support for all CPU features. For "
"instance **Intel**'s compiler doesn't provide separated flags for ``AVX2`` "
"and ``FMA3``, it makes sense since all Intel CPUs that comes with ``AVX2`` "
"also support ``FMA3``, but this approach is incompatible with other **x86** "
"CPUs from **AMD** or **VIA**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:286
msgid ""
"# Specify AVX2 will force enables FMA3 on Intel compilers\n"
"python setup.py build --cpu-baseline=avx2\n"
"# which equivalent to\n"
"python setup.py build --cpu-baseline=\"avx2 fma3\""
msgstr ""

