#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:341
msgid ""
":enabled:`Architecture`: The architecture name of target CPU. It should be "
"one of ``x86``, ``x64``, ``ppc64``, ``ppc64le``, ``armhf``, ``aarch64``, "
"``s390x`` or ``unknown``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:344
msgid ""
":enabled:`Compiler`: The compiler name. It should be one of gcc, clang, "
"msvc, icc, iccw or unix-like."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:347
msgid "**CPU baseline**:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:349
msgid ""
":enabled:`Requested`: The specific features and options to ``--cpu-"
"baseline`` as-is."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:350
#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:361
msgid ":enabled:`Enabled`: The final set of enabled CPU features."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:351
msgid ""
":enabled:`Flags`: The compiler flags that were used to all NumPy `C/C++` "
"sources during the compilation except for temporary sources that have been "
"used for generating the binary objects of dispatched features."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:354
msgid ""
":enabled:`Extra checks`: list of internal checks that activate certain "
"functionality or intrinsics related to the enabled features, useful for "
"debugging when it comes to developing SIMD kernels."
