"features for which optimizations have been generated are shown in the form "
"of several sections with similar properties explained as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:366
msgid ""
":enabled:`One or multiple dispatched feature`: The implied CPU features."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:367
msgid ":enabled:`Flags`: The compiler flags that been used for these features."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:368
msgid ""
":enabled:`Extra checks`: Similar to the baseline but for these dispatched "
"features."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:369
msgid ""
":enabled:`Detect`: Set of CPU features that need be detected in runtime in "
"order to execute the generated optimizations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/simd/build-options.rst:371
msgid ""
"The lines that come after the above property and end with a ':' on a "
"separate line, represent the paths of c/c++ sources that define the "
"generated optimizations."
